WEBVTT

00:01.580 --> 00:05.250
♪♪

00:05.250 --> 00:07.040
Mold on cheese
is fine, right?

00:07.040 --> 00:10.120
Isn't that
cheese's whole thing?

00:10.120 --> 00:11.540
Hey,
while you're in there,

00:11.540 --> 00:13.960
can you make room
for a 20-pound turkey?

00:13.960 --> 00:15.670
Uh, I don't know.

00:15.670 --> 00:16.790
Let me see.

00:20.120 --> 00:21.080
Done.

00:22.540 --> 00:25.380
What do we need a 20-pound
Thanksgiving turkey for?

00:25.380 --> 00:28.460
Well, I always go with
2 1/2 pounds per person.

00:28.460 --> 00:31.790
So, six meat-eaters --
there's your grandma, Bev --

00:31.790 --> 00:33.540
Going out of town.

00:33.540 --> 00:35.620
Oh, this is truly
a time to be thankful.

00:37.580 --> 00:38.750
What about Jackie?

00:38.750 --> 00:41.000
Mm, not gonna happen.
Or Becky.

00:41.000 --> 00:42.670
They're still furious at me

00:42.670 --> 00:44.500
about not letting them rent
The Lunch Box.

00:44.500 --> 00:46.620
Come on, Darlene.
What the hell's going on here?

00:46.620 --> 00:48.620
I thought I asked you
to fix all this.

00:48.620 --> 00:51.540
Hey, D.J., Mary, Mark, Harris --
they're all gonna be there.

00:51.540 --> 00:54.330
Sure, but they're all
boring.

00:54.330 --> 00:55.880
Alright, fine,
what about Odessa?

00:55.880 --> 00:59.330
She's not boring.
She's a thief and a pot head.

00:59.330 --> 01:01.670
Nope. I banned her
from the house.

01:01.670 --> 01:03.250
Oh, please.

01:03.250 --> 01:05.120
Just this one day,
I really cannot take

01:05.120 --> 01:06.960
any more of Harris
moping around here.

01:06.960 --> 01:08.380
[ Chuckling ]
Sure you can.

01:08.380 --> 01:10.380
The whole family spent
the last 40 years

01:10.380 --> 01:11.580
putting up
with your moping.

01:13.540 --> 01:14.960
You know, I always thought
if we had money,

01:14.960 --> 01:17.210
you'd be
clinically depressed.

01:17.210 --> 01:20.120
Oh, God,
that would've been sweet!

01:21.880 --> 01:24.170
Come on.
Let Odessa come.

01:24.170 --> 01:25.580
You know,
between the turkey and the weed,

01:25.580 --> 01:27.210
she's gonna be the first one
to pass out.

01:27.210 --> 01:30.290
Then we can draw on her face
with a Sharpie.

01:30.290 --> 01:31.460
I do like that.

01:31.460 --> 01:32.920
Then we are done here.

01:32.920 --> 01:35.210
Whoa.
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

01:35.210 --> 01:38.460
No, we are not done talking
about Jackie and Becky.

01:38.460 --> 01:40.380
Did you even try
to patch things up with them?

01:40.380 --> 01:42.710
Yes. I sent them
a really nice text.

01:42.710 --> 01:44.080
Let's hear it.

01:44.080 --> 01:45.080
Oh, sure.

01:46.750 --> 01:48.250
Um...

01:48.250 --> 01:49.330
"Hey, Jackie.

01:49.330 --> 01:52.420
I hate what this is doing
to our family.

01:52.420 --> 01:54.380
I love you and Becky
very much,

01:54.380 --> 01:56.670
despite your extreme
lack of awareness

01:56.670 --> 01:59.210
that your stupid idea could keep
this family in dire poverty

01:59.210 --> 02:02.000
for another 100 years.

02:02.000 --> 02:03.670
Sometimes,
dreams are nightmares.

02:03.670 --> 02:05.000
Please come
to Thanksgiving."

02:07.670 --> 02:09.420
See?
Doesn't matter what I say.

02:09.420 --> 02:11.920
Come on. You knew
that wasn't gonna work.

02:11.920 --> 02:14.170
Fine, but I have a right
to be mad, too.

02:14.170 --> 02:16.330
Just because Grandma Bev
gave me power of attorney,

02:16.330 --> 02:18.250
they're turning me
into some kind of villain.

02:18.250 --> 02:20.170
Look, all we have to do
is get everybody

02:20.170 --> 02:22.330
in the same room
together.

02:22.330 --> 02:23.960
We'll have
a couple of beers,

02:23.960 --> 02:25.960
we'll watch "Planes, Trains
and Automobiles."

02:25.960 --> 02:28.830
By the time John Candy says
"Those aren't pillows,"

02:28.830 --> 02:30.210
we'll be
a whole family again.

02:32.210 --> 02:34.040
That is
an awful lot of pressure

02:34.040 --> 02:37.000
to put on
a 30-year-old VHS tape.

02:37.000 --> 02:39.250
Well, until something better
comes along,

02:39.250 --> 02:41.210
we'll just have to be thankful
for what we have.

02:46.170 --> 02:47.620
Like our toaster brick.

02:55.500 --> 03:03.960
♪♪

03:03.960 --> 03:12.540
♪♪

03:12.540 --> 03:20.920
♪♪

03:20.920 --> 03:26.580
♪♪

03:29.290 --> 03:30.460
[ Knock on door ]

03:30.460 --> 03:31.620
"The Conners" is recorded

03:31.620 --> 03:33.670
in front of
a live studio audience.

03:33.670 --> 03:36.620
Hey, guys!
What are you doing here?

03:36.620 --> 03:39.580
We decided to come see the baby
on our way home from school.

03:39.580 --> 03:41.380
Isn't this pretty far
out of your way?

03:41.380 --> 03:43.420
Yeah, but I was
gonna take a picture

03:43.420 --> 03:45.420
of Beverly Rose
for Grandpa

03:45.420 --> 03:47.710
'cause he was saying
how sad it would be

03:47.710 --> 03:51.250
if he died and never had
a Thanksgiving with her.

03:51.250 --> 03:53.080
At least this way,
he can look at her picture.

03:53.080 --> 03:55.000
Ohh. That would be sad.

03:55.000 --> 03:56.250
Wouldn't it, Becky?

03:56.250 --> 03:57.710
It would be, Jackie.

03:57.710 --> 03:59.290
So sad!

04:01.000 --> 04:04.790
Unbelievable,
using the kids to guilt us.

04:04.790 --> 04:07.120
Okay, so, what's the next thing
you're supposed to say?

04:07.120 --> 04:09.500
I don't know
what you're talking about.

04:09.500 --> 04:13.000
I'm supposed to say that
since my mom's in Afghanistan,

04:13.000 --> 04:15.920
I really need
my whole family right now.

04:15.920 --> 04:18.710
But then I started to
think about my mom not
being there for real...

04:18.710 --> 04:21.920
[Voice breaking] and I'm really
sad, and I can't stop crying.

04:21.920 --> 04:23.830
Grandpa Dan might have
suggested the guilt,

04:23.830 --> 04:26.120
but the crying,
that's from Darlene, isn't it?

04:26.960 --> 04:27.920
Yeah.

04:30.170 --> 04:31.580
We really do
want you there.

04:31.580 --> 04:35.170
It sucks for the kids
when the adults are fighting.

04:35.170 --> 04:36.210
Please?

04:39.040 --> 04:40.120
I think we gotta.
[ Sighs ]

04:40.120 --> 04:41.620
Alright, fine,
we'll come.

04:41.620 --> 04:44.830
But you tell Grandpa Dan
that using kids isn't fair.

04:44.830 --> 04:46.040
And I want you to say

04:46.040 --> 04:48.000
that Aunt Jackie deserves
The Lunch Box

04:48.000 --> 04:50.080
and you're praying really hard
every night that she gets it.

04:51.790 --> 04:53.620
Grandpa Dan
gave us a dollar.

04:53.620 --> 04:55.080
What are you giving us?

04:56.620 --> 04:58.830
What about that stuff of Bev's
we were gonna toss?

04:58.830 --> 05:00.250
You mean the treasures?

05:02.290 --> 05:04.170
Grandma Bev
left some things here

05:04.170 --> 05:06.920
that we're keeping safe
in a trash bag,

05:06.920 --> 05:09.120
but let's pretend
that this is a mystery grab bag

05:09.120 --> 05:10.830
and whatever you pull out,
you get to keep.

05:12.460 --> 05:13.580
[ Gasps ]

05:13.580 --> 05:15.540
[ Gasps ] Ohh!
Ohh!

05:15.540 --> 05:18.000
You got the carved coconut
pirate head!

05:18.000 --> 05:20.170
She holds that when she talks
about her trip to the Caribbean.

05:20.170 --> 05:21.290
She's gonna miss that.

05:21.290 --> 05:22.120
Good pull!

05:24.540 --> 05:25.710
Louise: [ Chuckles ]

05:25.710 --> 05:29.080
I can't believe
you dug up our old yearbook.

05:29.080 --> 05:30.620
[ Chuckles ]
Look.

05:30.620 --> 05:32.290
Oh! Here's what I wrote
to you --

05:32.290 --> 05:35.670
"2-Good-2-B-4gotten."

05:35.670 --> 05:37.540
Yeah, I was really impressed
by the way you used

05:37.540 --> 05:40.620
the number 2 and the number 4
as words.

05:40.620 --> 05:42.750
I mean, Prince didn't start
doing that until way later.

05:42.750 --> 05:45.170
[ Laughs ]

05:45.170 --> 05:48.080
I just wanted people
to have a "bitchin' summer."

05:48.080 --> 05:49.500
[ Laughs ]

05:49.500 --> 05:52.500
Oh, look.
Here's what Roseanne wrote.

05:52.500 --> 05:54.960
"This girl is a woman now.

05:54.960 --> 05:58.710
See you in 2525
if man is still alive."

05:58.710 --> 06:01.500
[ Chuckles ] Wow.

06:01.500 --> 06:04.420
Sounds like you guys
had a pretty good summer.

06:04.420 --> 06:06.290
The best.

06:06.290 --> 06:08.420
Hey, what are your plans
for today?

06:08.420 --> 06:11.210
Well, thought I'd drag myself
to my sister's

06:11.210 --> 06:14.250
and listen to her brag
about how loaded they are

06:14.250 --> 06:16.250
that they can rent
a house boat

06:16.250 --> 06:18.790
on Lake of the Ozarks
every year.

06:18.790 --> 06:21.210
[ As bumpkin ] A house
what floats on the water?

06:21.210 --> 06:22.120
[ Laughs ]

06:22.120 --> 06:23.920
I reckon
you gotta be careful

06:23.920 --> 06:25.580
when you go to fetch
your newspaper.

06:25.580 --> 06:28.500
[ Chuckles ]

06:28.500 --> 06:30.500
Yeah, but I'm gonna
get her back this year.

06:30.500 --> 06:33.790
I'm giving her all my clothes
that I'm "too small for"

06:33.790 --> 06:35.960
right before dinner.

06:35.960 --> 06:37.750
"Enjoy your yams, Tiffany."

06:37.750 --> 06:39.250
[ Laughs ]

06:39.250 --> 06:41.380
Hey, why don't you save
that little gift for Christmas

06:41.380 --> 06:43.000
and join us
for dinner tonight?

06:43.000 --> 06:46.500
Hmm. You want me
at Thanksgiving?

06:46.500 --> 06:47.750
People will talk.

06:47.750 --> 06:49.580
Ah, let 'em talk.

06:49.580 --> 06:52.420
Besides,
I could use an ally.

06:52.420 --> 06:53.830
Things are a little tense
between the kids

06:53.830 --> 06:55.290
over The Lunch Box.

06:55.290 --> 06:58.330
Ah.
So, I'm a buffer.

06:58.330 --> 07:00.920
No, you're a friend!

07:00.920 --> 07:03.540
But as a friend,
if you want to be a buffer,

07:03.540 --> 07:05.540
I'll support you.

07:05.540 --> 07:07.540
You know, I have
a couple of pies in the car.

07:07.540 --> 07:09.330
I baked them for Tiffany,

07:09.330 --> 07:13.420
so the crusts are made of lard
and I doubled the sugar.

07:13.420 --> 07:15.500
I can't believe how well
this is turning out.

07:15.500 --> 07:16.620
[ Laughs ]

07:16.620 --> 07:21.120
♪♪

07:24.120 --> 07:26.380
I like how
none of your plates much.

07:26.380 --> 07:27.750
Thanks, Odessa.
That's what happens

07:27.750 --> 07:29.540
when you steal them
from different restaurants.

07:31.420 --> 07:33.920
Set another place.
Louise is joining us.

07:33.920 --> 07:35.380
-Hey.
-Hey.
-Hey!

07:35.380 --> 07:37.920
So, Grandpa,
where should Louise sit?

07:37.920 --> 07:40.000
By Odessa or next to you?

07:40.000 --> 07:41.380
Oh, yeah, Dad.

07:41.380 --> 07:43.210
Where do you want
Louise to sit?

07:44.420 --> 07:46.250
Well, she comes with pie,

07:46.250 --> 07:48.580
so I want her
next to me.

07:48.580 --> 07:50.790
And do you know what?
We're gonna give her
the good lawn chair.

07:50.790 --> 07:52.790
I'll hose it down
for spiders.

07:53.880 --> 07:55.330
Wow!

07:55.330 --> 07:58.330
How am I gonna go back
to my ordinary life?

07:58.330 --> 08:00.250
Well, it's 4:00.
Turkey should be ready.

08:00.250 --> 08:03.250
Let's not make this
any more unpleasant
than it has to be.

08:03.250 --> 08:04.250
Ohhh!

08:04.250 --> 08:06.960
Great. You're here.

08:06.960 --> 08:09.460
Hey, Jackie.
Nice to see ya.

08:09.460 --> 08:11.000
"Nice to see ya."
Classic.

08:13.580 --> 08:16.000
We hate Darlene.
This really isn't about you.

08:16.000 --> 08:17.670
Hey, Louise.

08:17.670 --> 08:19.000
Remember this?

08:38.920 --> 08:40.170
Huah!

08:40.170 --> 08:42.120
No, you don't remember it!

08:45.170 --> 08:47.540
'Cause nobody saw me
do my rifle routine

08:47.540 --> 08:49.880
senior year, 1974.

08:49.880 --> 08:52.500
I didn't get to do
the performance I
worked on for weeks

08:52.500 --> 08:55.920
because your garbage band
played too long.

08:55.920 --> 08:57.960
It's garage band.

08:57.960 --> 08:59.250
See ya at Christmas.

08:59.250 --> 09:00.790
No, what?
No, wait, wait, wait.

09:00.790 --> 09:02.330
Please, please, please --
hold on.

09:02.330 --> 09:04.000
Jackie, can I talk to you
for a minute?

09:05.710 --> 09:08.670
[ Exhales heavily ]

09:08.670 --> 09:11.210
Here's a hard truth
you've needed to hear
for some time now.

09:11.210 --> 09:13.500
Nobody wins a talent show
twirling a toy rifle.

09:13.500 --> 09:15.210
Never happened. Never gonna.
Move on!

09:19.120 --> 09:22.000
Fine. It's Thanksgiving.
I'll play nice.

09:23.420 --> 09:24.620
Sorry, Louise.

09:24.620 --> 09:27.420
Didn't mean to insult
your "garage" band.

09:28.920 --> 09:31.210
I appreciate that.

09:31.210 --> 09:33.960
You know, after high school,
that band went pro.

09:33.960 --> 09:36.290
I made a living off it
for 30 years.

09:36.290 --> 09:38.170
Yeah, well, we'll never know
where I would be now

09:38.170 --> 09:39.670
if people had seen
my rifle --

09:39.670 --> 09:41.710
Jackie, no!
What? What?!

09:45.380 --> 09:48.380
Lean right.
The left is mostly duct tape.

09:48.380 --> 09:50.790
Well,
time to start drinkin'.

09:50.790 --> 09:53.210
Brought some
Mexican social sauce

09:53.210 --> 09:55.500
if anyone cares
to join me.

09:55.500 --> 09:57.120
I'm in.
Alright.

09:57.120 --> 09:58.920
See, Darlene,
this is Bev's,

09:58.920 --> 10:00.670
and I'm in charge of it,

10:00.670 --> 10:03.330
but I'm still gonna share it,
'cause that's how it's done!

10:03.330 --> 10:05.420
Oh, that's
a really good point.

10:05.420 --> 10:07.830
A bottle of tequila is the same
as an inheritance.

10:07.830 --> 10:09.170
You can flush both
down the drain.

10:10.420 --> 10:11.750
Just for the record,

10:11.750 --> 10:14.000
I have never flushed tequila
down the drain.

10:15.670 --> 10:17.420
You know what? If you guys
are just looking for a fight,

10:17.420 --> 10:18.620
then you should just leave.

10:18.620 --> 10:20.170
Oh, no, no,
I'm not gonna be the bad guy

10:20.170 --> 10:21.620
that bails on Thanksgiving.

10:21.620 --> 10:25.120
No, this is a time
when families gather together

10:25.120 --> 10:28.120
to judge those who are selfish
and self-centered.

10:30.380 --> 10:32.540
I'm in. You're selfish
and self-centered.

10:32.540 --> 10:34.960
You're an old, bitter rat
in a curly wig.

10:38.080 --> 10:42.170
Sure would be a good time
for turkey, Dan.

10:42.170 --> 10:44.080
It should be just about ready.
Everybody, sit!

10:46.000 --> 10:48.380
Do you feel the tension?

10:48.380 --> 10:51.210
It's like something bad's
gonna happen.

10:51.210 --> 10:52.670
It's fantastic.

10:54.500 --> 10:56.580
Uh, bad news.

10:56.580 --> 11:01.380
325 in a 40-year-old oven
equals food poisoning.

11:01.380 --> 11:02.960
It's gonna be
a couple more hours.

11:05.250 --> 11:06.620
There it is.

11:06.620 --> 11:08.080
♪♪

11:12.120 --> 11:13.670
Can I help,
Daddy?

11:13.670 --> 11:15.670
Uh, no, this is
really delicate stuff, honey.

11:15.670 --> 11:16.620
I think I got it.

11:19.750 --> 11:21.000
She could've done that.

11:23.000 --> 11:24.210
We don't have to watch

11:24.210 --> 11:26.920
"Planes, Trains
and Automobiles."

11:26.920 --> 11:29.170
What about football? You don't
need a screwdriver for that.

11:29.170 --> 11:30.710
Great idea!

11:30.710 --> 11:32.620
[ Remote clicks ]

11:32.620 --> 11:35.330
Announcer: You know when a team
is down by six touchdowns,

11:35.330 --> 11:37.330
you really gotta salute
the few fans

11:37.330 --> 11:39.330
that are left in the stands.

11:39.330 --> 11:41.500
I don't know if my family
is still watching,

11:41.500 --> 11:44.250
but here's a shout-out
to my Meemaw.

11:44.250 --> 11:46.880
96 next week --
still going strong.

11:46.880 --> 11:48.830
Aww! To Meemaw!

11:48.830 --> 11:51.120
Sounds like a woman
who'd give her kid a restaurant.

11:53.460 --> 11:55.670
See ya.
Back before the turkey's ready.

11:55.670 --> 11:59.290
Wow! Somebody smells like weed
covered up poorly by Febreze.

12:00.670 --> 12:02.710
Oh, that's me.

12:02.710 --> 12:05.380
Kids, let's go in the kitchen
and check on the turkey.

12:05.380 --> 12:07.460
Uh, where do you think
you're going?
[ Remote clicks ]

12:07.460 --> 12:09.380
Odessa's place?

12:09.380 --> 12:10.960
No, you're not.
It's Thanksgiving.

12:10.960 --> 12:12.330
And why would you go
to Odessa's house

12:12.330 --> 12:13.790
when her parents
are out of town?

12:13.790 --> 12:16.290
You know, they're out of town
for, like, five years.

12:16.290 --> 12:17.380
[ Chuckles ]

12:17.380 --> 12:18.380
What?

12:18.380 --> 12:20.080
Oh.

12:20.080 --> 12:22.330
W-What are you
talking about?

12:22.330 --> 12:24.080
Okay,
I'm gonna tell you.

12:24.080 --> 12:25.540
Odessa lives by herself.

12:25.540 --> 12:27.170
Hard to believe.
She's so personable.

12:29.420 --> 12:31.880
I didn't say anything
because I knew you'd make
a big deal out of it,

12:31.880 --> 12:33.790
even though there's
absolutely no reason to.

12:33.790 --> 12:35.290
No reason?

12:35.290 --> 12:37.330
I let you spend the night there.
You lied to me.

12:37.330 --> 12:39.380
You didn't know her friend
lives alone? Good parenting.

12:39.380 --> 12:41.120
Shut up!

12:41.120 --> 12:42.540
Why do parents
need to be there?

12:42.540 --> 12:44.080
What do you think
we're doing?

12:44.080 --> 12:45.420
What are you doing?

12:45.420 --> 12:47.420
We make s'mores,
braid each other's hair,

12:47.420 --> 12:48.710
and dance around
in our underwear

12:48.710 --> 12:49.790
for men on the Internet.

12:49.790 --> 12:50.960
Problem?

12:50.960 --> 12:53.290
Hey,
don't be a smartass.

12:53.290 --> 12:54.830
Odessa's
a terrible influence.

12:54.830 --> 12:56.330
I didn't want her here
to begin with.

12:56.330 --> 12:57.830
Well, I'll fix that.

12:57.830 --> 12:59.000
Peace out, bitches.

13:03.000 --> 13:04.460
Is leaving an option?

13:04.460 --> 13:05.750
I-I didn't --

13:11.290 --> 13:14.420
Apparently, leaving is
only an option for strangers.

13:14.420 --> 13:16.170
If you're family,
you're trapped here.

13:16.170 --> 13:17.790
Oh, good.
You finally get it.

13:19.040 --> 13:21.420
I trust you, Harris.

13:21.420 --> 13:23.920
Then again, I'm not
a psycho control freak.

13:23.920 --> 13:25.830
Hey, you know what? You got
your own kid to screw up now.

13:25.830 --> 13:26.960
Stay away from mine.

13:26.960 --> 13:28.380
Hey,
take it down a notch.

13:28.380 --> 13:30.620
Hey, don't yell at Becky
'cause you're in over your head

13:30.620 --> 13:31.790
in all parts of your life.

13:31.790 --> 13:33.580
Oh! [ Laughs ]

13:33.580 --> 13:35.420
Hilarious coming from you.

13:35.420 --> 13:38.080
No, you know what's hilarious,
is the person

13:38.080 --> 13:40.880
who was sleeping around
and neglecting her kids

13:40.880 --> 13:43.920
is the one telling everybody
else how to live their life.

13:43.920 --> 13:46.710
Yeah, have another
glass of water, Jackie!

13:46.710 --> 13:48.420
Dilute
some of that tequila!

13:48.420 --> 13:51.290
This isn't tequila talking!
This is the truth!

13:51.290 --> 13:54.580
You think you're the almighty
decision-maker around here?!

13:54.580 --> 13:55.880
Huh?!

13:55.880 --> 13:57.750
You think you can
replace Roseanne

13:57.750 --> 13:59.290
as the mom
of this family?!

13:59.290 --> 14:00.290
What a joke!

14:00.290 --> 14:01.460
Jackie, enough!

14:01.460 --> 14:03.120
You want to talk
about my mom?

14:03.120 --> 14:04.960
Let's talk about her!

14:04.960 --> 14:08.250
'Cause she spent her entire life
trying to fix you,

14:08.250 --> 14:10.670
and every time she picked you
up, you fell down.

14:10.670 --> 14:11.880
You know why?

14:11.880 --> 14:13.210
'Cause you're a loser

14:13.210 --> 14:15.380
and you were
the bane of her existence!

14:15.380 --> 14:16.500
[ Gasps ]

14:16.500 --> 14:18.170
Don't you ever
touch my mother!

14:23.330 --> 14:25.500
Why did they
send us upstairs?

14:25.500 --> 14:27.210
We heard everything
from the kitchen.

14:27.210 --> 14:28.790
I want to know
what's going on.

14:28.790 --> 14:31.210
Get away from the door. You're
not supposed to hear that stuff.

14:34.710 --> 14:36.420
It's really quiet.

14:36.420 --> 14:39.540
I hope my mom
didn't kill Aunt Jackie.

14:39.540 --> 14:41.000
If she goes to prison,

14:41.000 --> 14:42.580
we'll be the family
with the mom in prison.

14:44.250 --> 14:46.790
Which is weird, because most
people have a dad in prison.

14:48.380 --> 14:51.920
All I know is, I think
Aunt Jackie's going crazy.

14:51.920 --> 14:53.540
They're all crazy.

14:53.540 --> 14:54.750
They're all old.

14:54.750 --> 14:56.330
Their lives didn't turn out
the way they thought,

14:56.330 --> 14:58.170
and now they're all
hitting each other.

15:05.670 --> 15:09.330
♪♪

15:09.330 --> 15:10.580
Wow.

15:10.580 --> 15:13.120
Beer and tequila going
from the house to the garage.

15:13.120 --> 15:16.080
It's the first time alcohol's
ever flowed in this direction.

15:16.080 --> 15:19.040
Well, I think
you made a wise decision.

15:19.040 --> 15:21.880
Call me crazy, but I don't think
the alcohol was helping.

15:21.880 --> 15:23.080
Neither was the buffer.

15:23.080 --> 15:25.000
You suck at this.

15:25.000 --> 15:26.750
Hey, you don't need
a buffer.

15:26.750 --> 15:29.040
You needed a riot cop
and some tear gas.

15:30.880 --> 15:32.750
Would you be upset
if I went home?

15:32.750 --> 15:34.380
Would you be upset
if I went with you?

15:34.380 --> 15:35.250
Run.

15:36.920 --> 15:37.710
Go.

15:44.790 --> 15:48.000
Here's what you gotta remember
when these things happen.

15:48.000 --> 15:49.920
Roll the beer
back and forth

15:49.920 --> 15:51.620
so you don't get
freezer burn.

15:54.830 --> 15:57.500
Look, I know
I said some ugly things,

15:57.500 --> 15:59.460
but Jackie said
some pretty ugly things, too.

15:59.460 --> 16:01.380
I mean, I can't believe
she slapped me.

16:01.380 --> 16:02.960
Really?

16:02.960 --> 16:05.330
I can't believe she waited
this long to slap you.

16:06.750 --> 16:08.710
What?
Think about it.

16:08.710 --> 16:11.330
As far as she's concerned,
you stole her inheritance.

16:11.330 --> 16:12.960
Well, that's her problem.

16:12.960 --> 16:14.210
No, it's our problem.

16:14.210 --> 16:15.000
The family's.

16:16.540 --> 16:18.500
And we're gonna work this out
right now.

16:19.580 --> 16:21.000
[ Groans ]

16:22.500 --> 16:23.960
Mark! Mary!

16:23.960 --> 16:25.620
Come on down
from the top of the stairs.

16:25.620 --> 16:28.330
I know you're up there
listening.

16:28.330 --> 16:30.210
I didn't want to spy,
but Mark made me.

16:30.210 --> 16:32.330
So hit him.

16:32.330 --> 16:34.620
Nobody's hitting anybody.

16:34.620 --> 16:36.540
Alright.

16:36.540 --> 16:38.170
In this corner,

16:38.170 --> 16:40.460
hailing from
Lanford, Illinois,

16:40.460 --> 16:42.380
the Sultan of Slap,

16:42.380 --> 16:44.710
the Antagonizing Aunt,

16:44.710 --> 16:46.670
the Queen of Crazy,

16:46.670 --> 16:47.920
Jackieeeeee...

16:47.920 --> 16:49.960
"Open Hand" Harris!

16:49.960 --> 16:51.540
You're not helping,
Dad.

16:51.540 --> 16:52.790
And in this corner,

16:52.790 --> 16:55.960
weighing in at 95 pounds
soaking wet --

16:55.960 --> 16:57.540
the Vicious Vegan,

16:57.540 --> 16:59.710
the Nasty Niece,

16:59.710 --> 17:02.330
the Raja of Retort,

17:02.330 --> 17:05.790
Darleeeene...

17:05.790 --> 17:08.330
"The Darkness" Conner!

17:08.330 --> 17:10.080
Alright, shake hands,
no low blows,

17:10.080 --> 17:11.790
and come out apologizing.

17:11.790 --> 17:13.170
[ Voice breaking ]
I'm so sorry, sweetheart.

17:13.170 --> 17:15.080
Are you okay?
Yeah.

17:15.080 --> 17:17.170
It's just that when
you were talking, I
was hearing my mother.

17:17.170 --> 17:19.210
I was slapping her,
not you.

17:20.620 --> 17:22.880
Yeah, it really felt like
you put your hip into it.

17:26.000 --> 17:28.120
You know, I shouldn't have said
those terrible things.

17:28.120 --> 17:29.460
I shouldn't have,
either.

17:29.460 --> 17:31.040
And I shouldn't have
enjoyed it so much.

17:33.250 --> 17:34.790
Alright.

17:34.790 --> 17:36.500
You two
want a restaurant.

17:36.500 --> 17:39.460
You want everybody to get
some money when Bev goes.

17:39.460 --> 17:41.710
There's gotta be
some kind of compromise here.

17:41.710 --> 17:45.380
I don't even care
about some stupid inheritance.

17:45.380 --> 17:47.670
I just want everyone
to get along.

17:47.670 --> 17:50.710
I don't care about
the stupid inheritance, either.

17:50.710 --> 17:52.880
Look, I'll be honest --
I could use that money.

17:52.880 --> 17:54.080
But it's not worth
all this.

17:54.080 --> 17:55.880
Alright.

17:55.880 --> 17:58.330
I'm willing to bet
on Jackie and Becky

17:58.330 --> 18:00.420
because I believe
in your ability

18:00.420 --> 18:01.880
and your desperation.

18:03.710 --> 18:04.790
I am desperate.

18:06.120 --> 18:07.080
Thanks, Dad.

18:08.790 --> 18:12.000
Well, I mean,
if that's how you all feel,

18:12.000 --> 18:14.040
I don't even know
who I'm fighting for --

18:14.040 --> 18:16.170
except me and Harris,
and I actually look forward

18:16.170 --> 18:17.880
to telling her
she just lost a lot of money.

18:19.540 --> 18:22.250
Majority rules.
You got yourself a restaurant!

18:22.250 --> 18:24.880
I'm gonna make this work
just to prove you wrong!

18:24.880 --> 18:26.790
Man, I hope you do.

18:26.790 --> 18:29.170
And I just want to say I really
appreciate you rolling over

18:29.170 --> 18:31.000
because you were forced to
by others.

18:32.540 --> 18:33.620
You are welcome.

18:33.620 --> 18:35.290
Can I hug you?
If you must.

18:35.290 --> 18:37.880
Okay, I'm gonna come in slow
on the left...

18:37.880 --> 18:40.920
[ Groaning ]
...and then tuck in
on the right nice and easy.

18:40.920 --> 18:42.710
Let me know
how the pressure is.
[ Groaning ] Oh, God.

18:42.710 --> 18:44.670
This is worse
than being hit.

18:44.670 --> 18:47.000
[ Chuckles ]

18:47.000 --> 18:49.500
Promise me we'll never fight
like this when we get old.

18:49.500 --> 18:51.120
Oh, I'm not getting old.

18:53.750 --> 18:55.500
Moving out. Bye.

18:55.500 --> 18:57.210
What?

18:57.210 --> 18:58.710
What are you
talking about?

18:58.710 --> 19:02.170
You guys are drunk and fighting
and slapping each other.

19:02.170 --> 19:04.500
And you can't trust me
to behave myself?

19:04.500 --> 19:06.170
Odessa just invited me
to live at her house.

19:06.170 --> 19:07.420
I'm out.

19:07.420 --> 19:09.500
You can't leave this house
till you're 18.

19:09.500 --> 19:10.790
Really?

19:10.790 --> 19:12.920
Because the only one fast enough
to catch me is Becky,

19:12.920 --> 19:13.960
and she's on my side.

19:13.960 --> 19:15.170
Holler!

19:17.960 --> 19:19.460
I'm going to Odessa's.

19:19.460 --> 19:21.040
Okay, whoa, whoa.

19:21.040 --> 19:22.960
E-Everybody slow down,
okay?

19:22.960 --> 19:24.120
It's been a bad night.

19:24.120 --> 19:25.540
Nobody's eaten.

19:25.540 --> 19:27.500
Apparently, there's not
gonna be any turkey.

19:27.500 --> 19:28.920
30 minutes away.

19:30.620 --> 19:32.120
45 at the most.

19:33.330 --> 19:36.290
So, it's fine if you go
to Odessa's tonight,

19:36.290 --> 19:37.830
but I want you back here
in the morning,

19:37.830 --> 19:39.290
and we are gonna talk.

19:39.290 --> 19:40.120
Whatever.

19:41.540 --> 19:42.880
[ Door closes ]
So that's it?

19:42.880 --> 19:44.500
You're just gonna let her
walk outta here like that?

19:44.500 --> 19:45.880
She has a friend
with an apartment.

19:45.880 --> 19:47.290
She might not come back.

19:47.290 --> 19:48.880
She just needs
to make a point.

19:48.880 --> 19:50.250
I mean, we all come back.

19:50.250 --> 19:51.710
Right, Becky?

19:53.000 --> 19:55.380
Hey,
I live with Jackie now!

19:55.380 --> 19:58.460
But I am...
moving back in tomorrow.

19:58.460 --> 20:01.330
Let's go...eat the skin
off that turkey!

20:01.330 --> 20:03.170
It should be
almost done by now.

20:05.420 --> 20:07.040
[ Exhales heavily ]

20:07.040 --> 20:09.580
Are you sure you're doing
the right thing with Harris?

20:09.580 --> 20:11.620
[ Scoffs ]

20:11.620 --> 20:12.670
No.

20:14.460 --> 20:16.290
You know, for the first time
in a long time,

20:16.290 --> 20:17.880
I wish you could
drink with me.

20:19.880 --> 20:22.500
You've ruined one life tonight.
Isn't that enough?

20:22.500 --> 20:25.040
♪♪

20:28.710 --> 20:31.250
Wow. I can't believe
you came back.

20:31.250 --> 20:33.540
I didn't come back
for you.

20:33.540 --> 20:34.960
These are my pies.

20:37.580 --> 20:39.040
How'd it go
at your sister's?

20:39.040 --> 20:41.580
Well, my brothers
got into a fistfight,

20:41.580 --> 20:43.000
took it out on the street,

20:43.000 --> 20:44.750
the cops came,

20:44.750 --> 20:46.290
and then
they tased my aunt

20:46.290 --> 20:48.040
while she was trying
to break it up.

20:50.210 --> 20:52.880
Wow! That's way better
than us!

20:52.880 --> 20:55.710
You said
there wasn't any pie left.

20:55.710 --> 20:57.460
There isn't.

20:59.210 --> 21:02.880
You're clearly
having a dream.

21:02.880 --> 21:04.710
No, I'm not!
I'm awake.

21:04.710 --> 21:06.750
My mom got slapped,
and my sister left.

21:06.750 --> 21:08.500
I deserve pie.

21:08.500 --> 21:12.080
Oh, Mark, Marky,
Mark, Mark, Mark, Mark.

21:12.080 --> 21:13.540
Here's the thing
about life --

21:13.540 --> 21:16.250
sometimes, bad things happen
and you still don't get pie.

21:17.670 --> 21:19.420
Oh, come here!
I'm kiddin'!

21:20.540 --> 21:21.960
Sit down.

21:21.960 --> 21:23.120
Watch me eat pie.
